The paper deals with recognizing irregular text in natural scene images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses an LSTM-based encoder-decoder framework, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural network components, which are commonly used in machine learning, falling under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with text recognition, which is a problem in information retrieval, falling under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
